properties.Name: WebSite
properties.Description: A website is a collection of Web pages, images, videos or other digital assets that is hosted on one or several Web server(s), usually accessible via the Internet, cell phone or a LAN.

Columns.Name: WebSiteUrl
Columns.Description: The URL associated with the web site. Often referred to as the domain name or registered domain name.

Columns.Name: HttpServerIpAddress
Columns.Description:
Internet Protocol number or address. A unique number consisting of 4 parts separated by dots, e.g. 165.113.245.2 

Every machine that is connected to the Internet must have a unique IP address at a point in time, though those IP addresses can be either static (i.e. fixed) or they can be dynamically allocated with the result that a website may have different IP addresses over time. If a machine does not have an IP number, it is not really on the Internet. Most machines also have one or more URLs or Domain Names that are easier for people to remember and which resolve to an IP address through the use of Name Servers.

Columns.Name: WebsiteName
Columns.Description: The title or name of the web site.

Columns.Name: WebsiteOwningPartyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Party.
